## The La Dissolution: The Rising Noise Floor

The La stage is the stage most immediately legible to a reader in the Si stage, because the Si stage inherited it. The La dissolution has four components, each of which increased the civilizational noise floor:

**1. The fracture of the corporate catching structure.** The Reformation, whatever its legitimate H₄₈-level grievances, dissolved the institutional container that had been holding the post-Incarnation catching network together at civilizational scale. Individual authority replaced corporate transmission. The Matthew 18:20 cross-term mechanism was not eliminated — it operated within the new Protestant communities — but it was fragmented. N people in many separate catching structures scales as √N against N people in a coherent one. The noise floor rose.

**2. The epistemological substitution.** The Scientific Revolution was not wrong about the power of H₄₈ measurement. Empiricism is the most powerful method available for questions where the phenomenon can be isolated, measured, and repeated. The substitution was wrong: replacing H₂₄ epistemology (catching-derived knowledge, concordance-validated, Reasonable [[Appendix I - Dictionary of Terms#Person|Person]] adjudicated) with H₄₈ epistemology as the sole standard. The domains most worth knowing about — what is real, what we are, what we owe each other — are exactly the domains H₄₈ measurement cannot reach. The epistemological substitution was the La stage performing the structural error that [[Appendix I - Dictionary of Terms#Reasonablenessism|Reasonablenessism]] (Paper 18) was written to name.

**3. The false signal proliferation.** The La stage generated false signals at unprecedented scale: nationalism, positivism, Marxism, various forms of utopian political ideology. Each of these passed the pragmatist test for a generation or a civilization because each drew on real substrate — genuine H₂₄ catching content that had been accumulated during the Sol stage and was now being repackaged in H₄₈-primary form. They worked until they didn't. The terminus of each false signal was catastrophic in proportion to the depth of the real substrate it had drawn on. The 20th century's catastrophes are the La-generated false signals reaching their termini simultaneously.

**4. The acceleration of the Heropass.** The La stage's technological development dramatically accelerated H₄₈ processing speed. The Heropass has always been merciless; it became, in the La stage, also fast. The window available to each individual for catching work did not change. The distraction environment competing for that window's attention became incomparably larger. This is the structural condition of the Si stage: not that catching is impossible, but that the signal-to-noise ratio at the individual level has never been lower in the recorded history of catching.

